<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="150" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="150">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia fastigiata" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fastigiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="150">Muhlenbergia fastigiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in South America in the Andean highlands of Argentina, Bolivia, Chile, Colombia, and Peru (
<bibRefCitation author="Morden, CW" journalOrPublisher="Nordic Journal of Botany" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" refId="B19" refString="Morden, CW, 1985. A biosystematic study of the Muhlenbergiarepens complex (Poaceae). PhD. Dissertation. Texas A&amp;M University, College Station." title="A biosystematic study of the Muhlenbergiarepens complex (Poaceae). PhD. Dissertation. Texas A &amp; M University, College Station." year="1985">Morden 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Morden, CW" journalOrPublisher="Sida" pageId="58" pageNumber="181" pagination="349 - 365" refId="B21" refString="Morden, CW, Hatch, SL, 1996. Morphological variation and synopsis of the Muhlenbergia repens complex (Poaceae). Sida 17: 349 - 365" title="Morphological variation and synopsis of the Muhlenbergia repens complex (Poaceae)." volume="17" year="1996">Morden and Hatch 1996</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="150" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="150">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="150">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia fastigiata" order="Poales" pageId="27" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fastigiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="150">Muhlenbergia fastigiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs on grassy flats, playas, slopes, rock outcrops, near gravelly creeks and lake margins in granitic and calcareous soils associated with 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Baccharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Baccharis" order="Asterales" pageId="27" pageNumber="150" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="150">Baccharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
